# Search Lab â€” Project Overview

A FastAPI-based **evaluation platform** for comparing OpenSearch search algorithms.
Engineers define algorithm configurations, build query libraries with ground-truth relevance
judgements, and run N-algorithm Ă— M-query benchmarks â€” measuring NDCG@K, MRR, Precision@K,
Recall@K, latency, and score separation. Results persist in MongoDB.

## Stack

- Python 3.14, uv (package manager), ruff (linter/formatter)
- FastAPI (async web framework), Pydantic v2 (schemas)
- OpenSearch 2.x (search engine â€” BM25, KNN, RRF)
- sentence-transformers (`all-MiniLM-L6-v2`, 384d) â€” local embedding model
- MongoDB + Motor (async) â€” benchmark result storage
- structlog (structured logging)
- pytest + pytest-asyncio (testing)

